---
import Base from '@layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Terms of Service — Echolia"
  description="Terms and conditions for using Echolia"
>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-12 md:py-16">
    <!-- Header -->
    <header class="mb-12 space-y-4">
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-semibold text-text-main">
        Terms of Service
      </h1>
      <p class="text-sm font-mono text-text-muted/70">
        Last updated: January 15, 2025
      </p>
      <p class="text-base md:text-lg text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
        We try to keep this simple. Use Echolia however you want, but be reasonable. We're not liable if something goes wrong, and you own everything you create.
      </p>
    </header>

    <!-- Content -->
    <article class="space-y-12 text-text-muted">
      <!-- TL;DR -->
      <section class="thought-card bg-bg-surface/50 space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-main flex items-center gap-2">
          <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-accent-pink" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 16h-1v-4h-1m1-4h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" />
          </svg>
          TL;DR
        </h2>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm leading-relaxed">
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-accent-pink">→</span>
            <span>Echolia is free to use for personal purposes</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-accent-pink">→</span>
            <span>You own all your content</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-accent-pink">→</span>
            <span>We're not liable if data loss occurs (back up your stuff)</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-accent-pink">→</span>
            <span>Don't use Echolia for illegal things</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-accent-pink">→</span>
            <span>Open source (MIT license) — you can modify it</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- The Agreement -->
      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-text-main pb-3 border-b border-white/5">
          The Agreement
        </h2>
        <div class="space-y-3 leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            By downloading and using Echolia, you agree to these terms. If you don't agree, don't use the app.
          </p>
          <p>
            We may update these terms occasionally. If we make significant changes, we'll let you know via the app, our website, or <a href="https://twitter.com/echolia_app" class="text-accent-pink hover:text-accent-cyan transition-colors underline">Twitter</a>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- License -->
      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-text-main pb-3 border-b border-white/5">
          License
        </h2>
        <div class="space-y-3 leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            Echolia is <strong class="text-text-main">free and open source</strong> software, licensed under the MIT License.
          </p>
          <p>
            This means you can:
          </p>
          <ul class="space-y-2 ml-4">
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-accent-pink flex-shrink-0">→</span>
              <span>Use it for personal or commercial purposes</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-accent-pink flex-shrink-0">→</span>
              <span>Modify the source code</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-accent-pink flex-shrink-0">→</span>
              <span>Distribute your own versions</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-accent-pink flex-shrink-0">→</span>
              <span>Fork it and build your own thing</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            The full MIT license is available in the <a href="https://github.com/echolia/echolia/blob/main/LICENSE" class="text-accent-pink hover:text-accent-cyan transition-colors underline">GitHub repository</a>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Your Content -->
      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-text-main pb-3 border-b border-white/5">
          Your Content
        </h2>
        <div class="space-y-3 leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            <strong class="text-text-main">You own everything you create in Echolia.</strong> Your thoughts, your words, your data — it's all yours.
          </p>
          <p>
            We don't claim any rights to your content. We can't even see it (since it's stored locally on your device).
          </p>
          <p>
            When sync launches (Q2 2025):
          </p>
          <ul class="space-y-2 ml-4">
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-accent-pink flex-shrink-0">→</span>
              <span>Your content will be end-to-end encrypted</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-accent-pink flex-shrink-0">→</span>
              <span>We'll only store encrypted blobs on our servers</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-accent-pink flex-shrink-0">→</span>
              <span>We still won't own or have access to your content</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Acceptable Use -->
      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-text-main pb-3 border-b border-white/5">
          Acceptable Use
        </h2>
        <div class="space-y-3 leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            We trust you to use Echolia responsibly. Don't use it for:
          </p>
          <ul class="space-y-2 ml-4">
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-text-muted/40 flex-shrink-0">✗</span>
              <span>Illegal activities</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-text-muted/40 flex-shrink-0">✗</span>
              <span>Harassing or threatening others</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-text-muted/40 flex-shrink-0">✗</span>
              <span>Distributing malware or viruses</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-text-muted/40 flex-shrink-0">✗</span>
              <span>Attempting to hack or break our servers (when sync launches)</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            Since Echolia is local-first, most of this doesn't apply — you're writing for yourself. But when sync launches, please don't abuse the service.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- No Warranties -->
      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-text-main pb-3 border-b border-white/5">
          No Warranties
        </h2>
        <div class="space-y-3 leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            Echolia is provided <strong class="text-text-main">"as is"</strong> without warranties of any kind.
          </p>
          <p>
            We work hard to make Echolia reliable, but we can't guarantee:
          </p>
          <ul class="space-y-2 ml-4">
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-text-muted/40 flex-shrink-0">→</span>
              <span>That it will be bug-free</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-text-muted/40 flex-shrink-0">→</span>
              <span>That it will work on all devices</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-text-muted/40 flex-shrink-0">→</span>
              <span>That updates won't break things</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-text-muted/40 flex-shrink-0">→</span>
              <span>That your data won't be lost</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-accent-pink text-sm">
            <strong>Important:</strong> Back up your data regularly. Use File → Export or manually copy your database file.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Limitation of Liability -->
      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-text-main pb-3 border-b border-white/5">
          Limitation of Liability
        </h2>
        <div class="space-y-3 leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            We're not liable for:
          </p>
          <ul class="space-y-2 ml-4">
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-text-muted/40 flex-shrink-0">→</span>
              <span>Lost data or content</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-text-muted/40 flex-shrink-0">→</span>
              <span>Business losses due to app downtime</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-text-muted/40 flex-shrink-0">→</span>
              <span>Damages from bugs or errors</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-text-muted/40 flex-shrink-0">→</span>
              <span>Issues caused by third-party software</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            In plain language: <strong class="text-text-main">We're not responsible if something goes wrong.</strong> Echolia is free software built by a small team. Use it at your own risk.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm">
            That said, if you encounter a bug, please <a href="https://github.com/echolia/echolia/issues" class="text-accent-pink hover:text-accent-cyan transition-colors underline">report it on GitHub</a>. We'll do our best to fix it.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Data Backup -->
      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-text-main pb-3 border-b border-white/5">
          Your Responsibility: Backups
        </h2>
        <div class="space-y-3 leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            Since Echolia is local-first, <strong class="text-text-main">you are responsible for backing up your data.</strong>
          </p>
          <p>
            We recommend:
          </p>
          <ul class="space-y-2 ml-4">
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-accent-pink flex-shrink-0">→</span>
              <span>Using the built-in export feature (File → Export)</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-accent-pink flex-shrink-0">→</span>
              <span>Copying your database file to cloud storage (Dropbox, iCloud, etc.)</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-accent-pink flex-shrink-0">→</span>
              <span>Exporting regularly if you have important thoughts</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            When sync launches, we'll handle encrypted backups. But until then, it's on you.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Termination -->
      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-text-main pb-3 border-b border-white/5">
          Termination
        </h2>
        <div class="space-y-3 leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            You can stop using Echolia at any time by:
          </p>
          <ul class="space-y-2 ml-4">
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-accent-pink flex-shrink-0">→</span>
              <span>Deleting the app</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-accent-pink flex-shrink-0">→</span>
              <span>Exporting your data first (recommended)</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-accent-pink flex-shrink-0">→</span>
              <span>Deleting your database file if you want to remove all traces</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            We may terminate or suspend access to sync services (when available) if you violate these terms. But since the app is local-first, you can continue using it offline.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Commercial Use -->
      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-text-main pb-3 border-b border-white/5">
          Commercial Use
        </h2>
        <div class="space-y-3 leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            You can use Echolia for commercial purposes (thanks to the MIT license). This includes:
          </p>
          <ul class="space-y-2 ml-4">
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-accent-pink flex-shrink-0">→</span>
              <span>Using it for work projects</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-accent-pink flex-shrink-0">→</span>
              <span>Running it on company computers</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-accent-pink flex-shrink-0">→</span>
              <span>Building your own version for your business</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            We don't offer enterprise support or SLAs, but you're welcome to use Echolia however you need.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Third-Party Services -->
      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-text-main pb-3 border-b border-white/5">
          Third-Party Services
        </h2>
        <div class="space-y-3 leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            Currently, Echolia doesn't integrate with any third-party services.
          </p>
          <p>
            When sync launches, we'll use:
          </p>
          <ul class="space-y-2 ml-4">
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-accent-pink flex-shrink-0">→</span>
              <span>Cloud storage for encrypted blobs (likely AWS S3 or similar)</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-accent-pink flex-shrink-0">→</span>
              <span>Those providers have their own terms of service</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            We're not responsible for third-party services, but we'll choose privacy-respecting providers.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Governing Law -->
      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-text-main pb-3 border-b border-white/5">
          Governing Law
        </h2>
        <div class="space-y-3 leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            These terms are governed by the laws of [Your Location — Update This].
          </p>
          <p>
            Any disputes will be resolved in [Your Location] courts.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-text-muted/80">
            (We hope it never comes to that. We're a small team building software we love. If you have issues, please <a href="mailto:hello@echolia.app" class="text-accent-pink hover:text-accent-cyan transition-colors underline">email us</a> first.)
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Changes to Terms -->
      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-text-main pb-3 border-b border-white/5">
          Changes to These Terms
        </h2>
        <div class="space-y-3 leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            We may update these terms as Echolia evolves. If we do:
          </p>
          <ul class="space-y-2 ml-4">
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-accent-pink flex-shrink-0">→</span>
              <span>We'll update the "Last updated" date</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-accent-pink flex-shrink-0">→</span>
              <span>We'll announce major changes on <a href="https://twitter.com/echolia_app" class="text-accent-pink hover:text-accent-cyan transition-colors underline">Twitter</a></span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-accent-pink flex-shrink-0">→</span>
              <span>Continued use means you accept the new terms</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Contact -->
      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-text-main pb-3 border-b border-white/5">
          Questions?
        </h2>
        <div class="space-y-3 leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            If you have questions about these terms:
          </p>
          <ul class="space-y-2 ml-4">
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-accent-pink flex-shrink-0">→</span>
              <span>Email: <a href="mailto:legal@echolia.app" class="text-accent-pink hover:text-accent-cyan transition-colors underline">legal@echolia.app</a></span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-accent-pink flex-shrink-0">→</span>
              <span>Twitter: <a href="https://twitter.com/echolia_app" class="text-accent-pink hover:text-accent-cyan transition-colors underline">@echolia_app</a></span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-accent-pink flex-shrink-0">→</span>
              <span>GitHub: <a href="https://github.com/echolia/echolia/discussions" class="text-accent-pink hover:text-accent-cyan transition-colors underline">Discussions</a></span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </section>
    </article>

    <!-- Footer Note -->
    <div class="mt-16 pt-8 border-t border-white/5">
      <div class="thought-card bg-bg-surface/30 space-y-3 text-center">
        <p class="text-sm text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
          We wrote these terms in <strong class="text-text-main">plain language</strong> because legalese is exhausting.
        </p>
        <p class="text-xs text-text-muted/70">
          The spirit: <em class="text-accent-pink">Use Echolia however you want, own your data, and we're not responsible if things break.</em>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
